<br>
this is about outnuking, not outdamaging. pets are not an issue in that discussion. <br>
<br>
<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
WRONG.<br>
<br>
If pets sucked total ass and only did...I don't know. 5 dps, I would be *HIGHLY* against wizards having nukes that were 30-40% more efficient than mage's.<br>
<br>
However, they are not. Mages have pets that can do upwards of 75-80dps for the cost of summoning their epic.<br>
<br>
You can pretty much throw out the majority of our non-offensive spells. Mages can debuff &amp; DS. Wizards can root &amp; snare. Mages have semi-useful summons. Wizards have semi-useful ports.<br>
<br>
When comparing wizards to mages, I've personally always felt this was fair:<br>
<br>
Mage: 70% efficiency of a wizard's best nukes, 80% of their DPS. Pets should make up about 30% of whatever a wizard's DPS is.<br>
<br>
So...<br>
<br>
If a wizard has the following spell as their bread and butter at 65 (i made this up):<br>
<br>
3000 damage, 600 mana, 10.0 second cast time.<br>
<br>
(5.0 dmg / mana, 300 dps)<br>
<br>
Mages should get something along the lines of:<br>
<br>
2000 damage,   570 mana, 8.4 second cast time<br>
<br>
(3.5 dmg / mana, 240 dps)<br>
<br>
And their pet would do 100 dps, for a total of 340 dps<br>
<br>
(this is level 65, mind you people thinking 'those numbers are way too high!)<br>
<br>
this would give mages a nice edge in most situations, with a slight hit should they lose their pet or it dies or you were raiding a really really small mob (seru?). obviously mages would do better in high resist situations, and wizards would do better in high damage mitigation situations.<br>
<br>
<br>
