<br>
I have seen the arguments that: &quot;Hey, without ID4 item, this isn't so great&quot;.   Same can be said about all lvl 61 - 65 wiz nukes too.   So that doesn't wash.<br>
<br>
Rather than continue the rants, what alternative solutions are there?<br>
<br>
A) Add 2 or 3 wiz vendor nukes (one of them must be cold) that is capable of doing 30 - 40 percent more DPS than FoT.  Needs to be slightly better on dmg/mana ratio too.<br>
<br>
B) Change FoT to be something more inline, and make a FoT clone spell as a lvl 65 drop as difficult/easy as GSS/EER.  Note, you cannot take away scribed spells so you have to change the existing one.  My reasons for this is that the one of the major beefs that wiz have is the ease at which a spell of this power can be procured.<br>
<br>
C)  Add 3 damage focus vendor based spells to wiz to allow the DPS of comparable (in availability) to do the 30 - 40 percent more in DPS.<br>
<br>
I am not speaking to Pet dmg or DS.  I know many wizards are against having any sort of useful pet/buff/DS and I understand this.<br>
<br>
Feel free to add &quot;viable&quot; alternatives if you have them.  I am just listing ones that I see.  My choice would be either A) or C).<br>
