AvgWiz -- lvl 62 sorceror <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ravilicuslolf>Ravilicus LoLF</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 468<br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/1/02 11:11 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Talon on a vendor. Not cool(Serious discussion only)</span><hr size=1> One aspect of this discussion focuses on the influence of FoT on pure DPS/efficiency.<br>
<br>
With PoP and retuning of encounters, one of the bigger limitations to DPS, aggro control, is not nearly as strong a concern.  The fact that many PoP &quot;yard trash&quot; mobs have relatively low Hit points for their level makes powerful nukes and high DPS that much more excellent.  It is reminisent of Pre-lvl 60 cap, when Ice Comet would tear most mobs a near arse, but requiring a good delay before being cast.<br>
<br>
My solution to the &quot;issue&quot; of the supposed imbalance created by having a high DPS spell so readilly available isn't to &quot;fight fire with fire&quot; as it were, but does consider availability as a factor.<br>
<br>
What I would lik to see is a spell that gives us even better use of the spells we currently have.  I like what Verant did with Ice Flame, and focus items, and AA.  These were brilliant ideas, and the implementation hasn't been TOO bad.  What I would like to see is a supplement to this, and a new Wizard-only line of self buffs.<br>
<br>
The new line of spells wouldn't be an augmentation of damage, or spell casting time, or distance, or mana usage - instead it would produce a buff which reduces the aggro generated by the Wizard.<br>
<br>
Currently there are AA abilities and buff spells by enchanters that provide similar effects, but with the exception of the Concussion spell there is nothing a Wizard can do directly to control aggro except wait for those around him to produce more of it themselves.  The idea is to enable to Wizards to nuke harder earlier.  If there were a line of Wizard self only buffs which reduced the aggro generated by the Wizard's spells, the Wizard would then be able to start doing GREATER amounts of damage SOONER in a fight, therefore increasing their DPS (mana allowing).  The buff could even have a limited duration, so long as the duration is balanced with it's casting cost and casting time.<br>
<br>
The benefit of the buff line would be obvious, it is unresistable in it's effect, therefore reliable and powerful.  It doesn't aid soloers in the least.  The drawback of using it could be not only in the mana used in casting it, but it could also have a NEGATIVE focus effect, such as ADDING an additional 5% or whatever to the casting cost of any detrimental spell.  The effect of the buff could even be made to be a random amount of aggro reduction, so as to be somewhat unreliable, but still worth using if the Wizard wants to take the risk of doing substantial damage which would normally put her in harms way.<br>
<br>
This spell line could be vendor bought, and scale up in power through the levels. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wandork>Wandor K</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer<BR>Warriors ph34r me!<BR>Gnomercy for Gno-one!</span><br>  Posts: 1524<br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/1/02 1:09 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Talon on a vendor. Not cool(Serious discussion only)</span><hr size=1> Holy shit break out the kleenex! Is it even possible to whine more?<br>
<br>
First of all, stop discounting the fact that FoT is a bolt. This is the #1 disadvantage to this spell. For this spell to be anywhere near as effective as Sunstrike a mage has to have line of sight to the mob. Pets and people eat a lot of bolts, which totally screws DPS. No matter what you say, bolts are highly situational because of their innate ability to miss.<br>
<br>
Next, stop factoring in AAs to make the spell look better. If you want to factor those in you will lose because wizards have a much higher crit rate with AAs than is even possible with a mage. The don't get SCFM ever so we have 2% innate + 6% SCFM for a total of 8% more chance to crit. This far outweighs the fact that mages can crit higher until level 63.<br>
<br>
Don't forget that FoT is spec EVOCATION and every mage in Norrath with half a brain chose spec CONJURATION. Again, you can't factor in AAs because SCM3 is obtainable by either a wiz or a mage and both having the skill cancels any increase in power since it's the same for both classes. At any rate, the simple fact that this is an evocation spell means that we get an additional 9% mana savings on every cast.<br>
<br>
You can also toss out the mages can debuff fire argument becuase this helps us out as well. Not only that, but if you want to include the fire debuff, then mages are losing efficiency and DPS becuase they have to cast the debuff, which last time I checked, cost mana, took time to cast, and generated agro. Our spells have an INNATE lower resistance check that stacks with any debuffing done by any class. The fact is we have a lower resistance rate than mages do no matter what the situation is because our spells are designed that way. Any advantage a mage would gain by debuffing is negated by the fact that it helps us too!<br>
<br>
Another fact that everyone seems to be completely ignoring that mages only get fire and magic spells and that our magic spells are far superior to their magic spells. If cold nukes are called for a mage gets to sit on their ass and watch their pet be their only source of damage.<br>
<br>
Discounting agro management is completely assinine as well. Granted, in the kill it as fast as you can enoucnter in PoP, its not as important for us wizards because we get self runes. Be it our epic or manaskin, we still have the advantage of having a rune to give us a little room for error. Maybe you are forgetting that these mobs that die fast also hit like Mack trucks. If any mob in PoV gets ahold of you, you better pray you lose agro before the mob gets a second round in or you are dead. Triple 500s hurt a lot more when you don't have an 800 pt buffer and an agro reducing spell that will help get mobs off you. If a mage gets agro in PoP, chances are they are toast in 2 rounds of combat so agro management suddenly becuase a lot more important to them. They have to depend on someone else regaining agro to save them, we get skins and concussion to buy us extra time and reduce our agro. A dead mage has 0 DPS.<br>
<br>
And last, but certainly not least ... who ever said that we are entitled to having our spells on a vendor? Would I like to see some of our nukes on a vendor? I sure would! But am I going to whine just because mages got lucky? No, I am going to be happy for them, any class getting an upgrade benefits me on a raid so the more people getting bones from SOE, the better. <p><div align="center" class="font-size: 11px; font-family: arial">
