<br>
There are too many factors here to properly compare FoT with any of our wizard spells (as Milaru and Oxoxo are continually illustrating).  Bolt vs. DD, aggro, DPS, crits...no way to balance these out.  So, instead of comparing apples to oranges, I think we should compare each of our merchant bought 61 spells with each of their predecessors.<br>
<br>
Bolt of Tallon (61 mage bolt) vs.Seeking Flame (59 mage bolt)<br>
<br>
BoT = 1920 damage/500 mana (3.84 ratio), casting time 7.0 sec (274 DPS).<br>
SFoS = 1024 damage/320 mana (3.20 ratio), casting time 7.0 sec (146 DPS)<br>
<br>
Compare the two, and you find <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Bolt of Tallon has 20% better efficiency and 88% better DPS.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Lure of Thunder (61 wizard) vs. Lure of Ice (60 wizard)<br>
<br>
LoThu = 1070 damage/378 mana (2.83 ratio), casting time 4.5 sec (238 DPS).<br>
LoIce = 825 damage/320 mana (2.58 ratio), casting time 4.5 sec (183 DPS)<br>
<br>
Compare the two, and you find <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Lure of Thunder has 10% better efficiency and 23% better DPS.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Ok, so conclusion time.  The increase in power Mage's get with their Bolts is <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>more than double</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> the increase in power we get with our Lures.<br>
<br>
